  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And according to, to my hearings, to my knowledge, it's over 150,000, 200,000 Jews lived in, in Hungary.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] the majority was executed mostly-- according, again, to my-- to what I heard, because I wasn't in Hungary when the real atrocities begun.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They, they started killing Jews fair dinkum when the Hungarian [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] you could call-- it wasn't the hakenkruis.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a different kruis.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was the Arrows, the, the Four Arrows.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They were the Hungarian fascist parties.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they started collecting Jews and shoot them in the Danube.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But by the time when this started, I, I was a long time ago already in Germany doing my own things with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Certain houses where not too many Jews lived, they moved the Jews out.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they moved into buildings where a lot of Jews lived.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So they made Jewish houses.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Most probably, according to my knowledge today, they did that because they wanted to concentrate Jews into buildings so later on, if they deporting them, they, they are much easier to get them than when they are scattered around and mixed up.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But at the moment, I have a non-Jewish friend here from Hungary whom I met just here in Ha-Koah Club.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he told me answering your questions that opposite us was also a Jewish house where only a few non-Jews lived.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they had sign in they doors-- on they doors, that in this flat, non-Jews are living, which I didn't know those time, because that time we lived-- I lived in a, a, a house where only Jews were.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So we didn't know what the Christians were doing, how they live or what they doing or whatever.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
